cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with wireless communication systems and resource allocation for vehicular networks. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests a possible fit with the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and probabilistic analysis, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of deep learning for CSI estimation also suggests a possible fit with the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
